contentrichtext.text: '''Edward Fitzgerald''' may refer to: *[[Edward Fitzgerald (1529-90)]], MP for [[Great Grimsby (UK Parliament constituency)]] and Lichfield * [[Lord Edward FitzGerald]] (1763–1798), Irish revolutionary * [[Edward Fitzgerald (insurgent)]] (1770?–1807), Irish revolutionary * [[Edward FitzGerald, 7th Duke of Leinster]] (1892–1976) * Edward Fitzgerald, [[Lord Mayor of Cork]] in 1901 and 1902 * [[Edward Fitzgerald (barrister)]], English barrister * [[Edward FitzGerald (poet)]] (1809–1883), English writer * [[Edward Fitzgerald (adviser)]], American adviser to Senator Claude Pepper * [[Edward Fitzgerald (ice hockey)]] (1891–1966), American ice hockey player * [[Edward Fitzgerald Beale]] (1822–1893), American naval officer, frontiersman and diplomat * [[Edward FitzGerald (mountaineer)]], leader of first group to climb [[Aconcagua]] * [[Edward Fitzgerald (Texas politician)]], see [[Texas Senate, District 19]] * [[Edward Aloysius Fitzgerald]] (1893–1972), fourth bishop of the Roman Catholic Diocese of Winona * [[Edward Fitzgerald (bishop)]] (1833–1907), second bishop of the Roman Catholic Diocese of Little Rock * [[Ed Fitz Gerald]] (born 1924), American baseball player * [[Edward E. Fitzgerald]] (1919-2001) sports writer, editor [[Sport (US magazine)|Sport magazine]], chief executive of [[Book of the Month Club]] * [[Edward Fitzgerald (brewer)]] (1820-1896), Australian brewer * [[Edward FitzGerald (Ohio politician)]], County Executive of [[Cuyahoga County, Ohio]] ==See also== * [[SS Edmund Fitzgerald|SS ''Edmund Fitzgerald'']], an American Great Lakes freighter {{hndis|Fitzgerald, Edward}}
